1 5. An individual may register to vote on the day of an election by completing the
2 prescribed form and submitting the required information at the appropriate polling
3 place.
4 6. Upon receipt of a registration form, properly filled out and signed by the applicant, the
5 county auditor or authorized election officer shall register the individual as a qualified
6 elector in the central voter file.
7 7. The secretary of state shall prescribe the forms to be used for registration of qualified
8 electors which must include the qualified elector's name, address, date of birth, last
9 place of registration, and any other information the secretary of state determines to be
10 necessary to assure accurate and reliable qualified elector registration.
11 8. The director of the department of transportation shall cooperate with the secretary of
12 state to develop voter registration forms to be used with a driver's license or
13 nondriver's identification card application and renewal and a change of name and
14 address request.
15 9. A designation of political party affiliation may not be noted or indicated on the
16 registration form.
17 10. The secretary of state shall adopt rules and prescribe the forms to be used for transfer
18 of electors within the central voter file and the deletion of electors from the central
19 voter file.
20 11. Subject to rules adopted by the secretary of state, the registration of a qualified elector
21 is permanent.
